# CHANGELOG - ORIC-1 Emulator

All notable changes to this project will be documented in this file.

The format is based on [Keep a Changelog](https://keepachangelog.com/en/1.0.0/),
and this project adheres to [Semantic Versioning](https://semver.org/spec/v2.0.0.html).

## [Unreleased]

### Planned
- 6502 CPU cycle-accurate implementation
- Memory management system
- VIA 6522 I/O controller
- Video system (text and hires modes)
- AY-3-8910 audio chip
- Storage support (.TAP, Sedoric)
- Host filesystem sharing
- Conversion tools (BASIC/machine → .TAP/Sedoric)

## [0.1.0-alpha] - 2026-01-31

### Added
- Project repository initialization
- Directory structure for modular architecture
- Agile project management documentation
- VERSION_TRACKING system
- CHANGELOG file
- ROADMAP document
- Git configuration (user: bmarty, email: bmarty@mailo.com)
- Build system structure (CMake support planned)
- Test framework structure
- Documentation skeleton

### Architecture
- Modular design: CPU, Memory, I/O, Video, Audio, Storage, HostFS
- Separation between emulator core and utilities
- Test-driven development structure
- Documentation-driven development approach

### Development Setup
- C/C++ project structure
- Unit and integration test directories
- API, specifications, and user guide documentation structure
- Tools directory for conversion utilities

